GIICHI KENOSHITA, Appellant, v. A. E. BURNETT, District Director of Immigration, District No. 31, Appellee. No. 7228. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. July 27, 1933. J. E. Keating and T. E. Bowen, both of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., and Clyde Thomas, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Los An-geles, Cal., for appellee.

Before SAWTELLE, Circuit Judge, and NORCROSS, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of appellee, ordered appeal herein dismissed for failure of appellant to file reeord and docket cause; mandate forthwith.
